list.item:
It would offer an opportunity for U.S. influence to be thrown
                                against unwise actions which the Committee might otherwise
                                take;

It would prevent the accusations, which are certain to develop,
                                that the United States is indifferent to the fate of dependent
                                peoples;

It will be interpreted as lending U.S. support to claims for disputed
                            territories with regard to which we have always maintained an impartial
                            attitude;

It will, if carried on by the U.S. representative consistently with
                            the principles we have always expressed, actually antagonize the Latin
                            Americans more than if we abstained;
